Purpose
This folder is used to store cached versions of ad-blocking lists for the HootGuard system. These lists are fetched from external sources (e.g., GitHub) and saved here to improve performance and reduce reliance on continuous network access.

How It Works
Caching: When the system fetches a blocking list, it checks if a cached version exists in this directory.
Expiry: Cached files remain valid for up to one week. After that, they are refreshed by fetching the latest version from the source.
File Naming: Each cached file is named based on the blocking list profile. For example:
  enhanced.txt: Cache for the "enhanced" blocking list.
  social.txt: Cache for the "social" blocking list.

Do Not Delete
Deleting this folder or its contents will force the system to fetch all blocking lists again, which may cause unnecessary network traffic and delays.
If the folder must be cleared for any reason, ensure that the system has internet access to re-download the lists.

Maintenance
The system automatically manages and updates the cache.
No manual intervention is needed.
